<h4> <b>Which  rules  govern  pension  and  gratuity  to  the  employees retiring  from  Central Government Civil Departments?</b></h4></li></b>


   <h4> Pension  and  gratuity  of  the  employees retiring  from  Central  Government  Departments is regulated  by the  Central  CivilServices  (Pension)  Rules,  1972.  There  are  separate  rules
regarding pension and gratuity of Railway employees and Defence personnel.</h4>
 </div>
<br>

<div class="content1b">
<b> <li><h4><b>Is the date of voluntary retirement treated as duty?</b></h4>
</li></b>


<h4>Yes, the date of voluntary retirement is treated as duty (Rule 5).</h4>
</div>

<br>

<div class="content1c">
<b> <li><h4><b>Who is eligible for pension?</b> </h4></li></b>


<h4>A Govt. servant appointed in  a pensionable establishment on or before  31.12.2003 and retires from Government service with a qualifying service of 10 years or more is eligible for pension (Rule 2, 49).</h4>
</div>
